From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|loud|lang=enm}}, {{term|lud|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|hlud|hlūd|loud, noisy, sounding, sonorous|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|gem-pro|hlūþaz|heard|lang=en}}, from {{proto|ine-pro|ḱlewtos|heard, famous|lang=en}}, from {{proto|ine-pro|ḱlew-|to hear|lang=en}}. Akin to {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|loud|lang=sco}}, {{term|lowd||loud|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|lûd||loud|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|luid||loud|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|lud||loud|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|laut||loud|lang=de}}, {{etyl|ga|-}} {{term|clú||repute|lang=ga}}, {{etyl|cy|-}} {{term|clywed||heard|lang=cy}}, {{term|clod||praise|lang=cy}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|inclutus||famous|lang=la}}, [[Tocharian]] A/B ''klots/klautso'' 'ear', ''klyostär'' 'heard', {{etyl|grc|-}} {{term|κλυτός||famous|tr=klútós|lang=grc}}, {{etyl|sq|-}} {{term|quaj||to name, call|lang=sq}}, {{term|shquar||famous, notorious|lang=sq}}, {{etyl|xcl|-}} {{term|լու|tr=lu||the act of hearing|lang=xcl}}, {{etyl|cu|-}} {{term|слава||glory|tr=slava|lang=cu}}, {{term|слово||word|tr=slovo|lang=cu}}, {{etyl|sa|-}} {{term|श्रव||glory|tr=śráva|lang=sa}}. More at [[listen]].

